            "explain": "The universal property: $f\\colon X \\to Y$ descends to a (unique) $\\bar f\\colon X/{\\sim} \\to Y$ with $\\bar f \\circ \\pi = f$ exactly when $f$ respects the equivalence — i.e. $x \\sim x' \\Rightarrow f(x) = f(x')$."
